content:
Manage AI Models in Einstein Studio
Users can create, update, and delete models with the new Allow users to manage models in Einstein Studio permission, which is available for permission sets.

Power Your Generative AI Using Anthropic Models with Prompt Builder
Accelerate your business goals with the hyper-intelligent and fast Anthropic models hosted on Amazon Bedrock. Use your model with Prompt Builder and other apps to deliver generative AI for your use case.

Power Your Generative AI with Google Gemini and Prompt Builder
Use the reliable, efficient, and highly intelligent Google Gemini model to drive your generative AI use cases. Leverage the power of your Salesforce data and use the insights to deliver innovative solutions for your customers.

Leverage Alerts to Evaluate the Quality of Your Predictive Model
Einstein Studio provides alerts to help you manage data discrepancies and issues that can occur during model training. Act on and resolve your alerts to build, retrain, and deploy models that can deliver more accurate predictions.

Let Einstein Autoselect the Best Factors for Your Use Case
Einstein saves you time and intelligently selects the most relevant variables and recommended algorithm for a use case.

Evaluate Your Model Performance with Activity Metrics
Use activity metrics to understand the performance of your predictive or generative model. View a summary of the total number of inferences over different time periods and gain insights into your connection, timeout, and authentication errors.

Access Models Quicker with the Updated Einstein Studio Navigation
You can now access models from a centralized location. Use the sidebar to locate models and open the model library.
